<section id="1002J_S0010" variety="S0010">
<name>BRAKE CONTROL</name>
<ttl id="1002J_S0010_72Z6O_T00AN" variety="T00AN">
<name>VEHICLE STABILITY CONTROL SYSTEM (for ADVICS Made)</name>
<para id="RM000000XIE009X" category="C" type-id="300AA" name-id="BC1N2-01" from="200601">
<dtccode>C1249/49</dtccode>
<dtcname>Open in Stop Light Switch Circuit</dtcname>
<subpara id="RM000000XIE009X_01" type-id="60" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___00005N400000">
<name>DESCRIPTION</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<ptxt>The skid control ECU (housed in the actuator assembly) inputs the stop light switch signal and the condition of brake operation.</ptxt>
<ptxt>The skid control ECU has an open detection circuit, which outputs this DTC when detecting an open in the stop light input line while the stop light switch is OFF.</ptxt>
<table pgwide="1">
<tgroup cols="3">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="1.00in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="3.14in"/>
<colspec colname="COL3" colwidth="2.94in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>DTC No.</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>DTC Detection Condition</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Trouble Area</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>C1249/49</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>When IG1 terminal voltage is 9.5 to 17.2 V, an open circuit of the stop light switch continues for 0.3 seconds or more.</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<list1 type="unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>STOP fuse</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>Stop light switch</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>Stop light switch circuit</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>Brake actuator assembly (Skid control ECU)</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</content5>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM000000XIE009X_02" type-id="32" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___00005N500000">
<name>WIRING DIAGRAM</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="C136030E01" width="7.106578999in" height="8.799559038in"/>
</figure>
</content5>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM000000XIE009X_03" type-id="51" category="05" proc-id="RM0250U___00005N600000">
<name>INSPECTION PROCEDURE</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<atten3>
<ptxt>When replacing the brake actuator assembly, perform zero point calibration (See page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM000000XHR009X"/>).</ptxt>
</atten3>
